The boys golf triangular scheduled for today at the Madison Golf and Country Club has been CANCELLED because of the flooding at the golf course.

May 28, 2019 at 4:30 PM ·

Here is a great running camp for any CC runners interested! :)

Madison Physical Therapy
May 28, 2019 at 2:03 PM ·

**ATTENTION ALL 7th-12th GRADE RUNNERS!**

We will be hosting a Distance Running Day Camp on Saturday JUNE 15th, 2019 from 8am to 3pm at Dakota State University Trojan Field House. Lunch will be provided, please bring running shoes/attire for the day, water bottle and sunscreen(if desired). Registration can be done the day of the event! All Attendees MUST complete an application to participate.

What to expect?! We invite you to join us for an exciting and informative Day Camp featuring DSU Head Cross Country/Track and Field Coach and Conference Coach of the Year, Anthony Drealan for information on summer training, strength training, injury prevention, gait analysis/footwear education and more!

Madison Bulldogs High School Baseball
April 22, 2019 at 10:36 PM ·

Bulldogs sweep W/WS/SC 10-0 and 7-0. Game 1 Mitch Williams had 3 hits, and Evan Appelwick had 3 RBI and a Home Run. Tyler Tappe pitched 6 strong innings giving up 1 hit while striking out 12.
Game 2 Appelwick had 2 more hits. Aspen Dahl got the win throwing 5 innings, giving up 1 hit while striking out 11.
Bulldogs move to 8-2 and 5-0 in the Region.
Next up is ORR at home on Wednesday, 6pm first pitch.

145 Colby Mennis defeats TJ Morrison 6 to 5 will wrestle Eli Kadoun of Sioux Falls Roosevelt for championship
152 Nolan Johnson pins Tyson Lien of Huron will wrestle Cooper Voorhees of Rapid City Stevens for championship

Awesome round for the Bulldogs!!

MHS BASEBALL ANNOUNCEMENT:
High School Baseball will hold it's first practice this Sunday, January 13th from 7-9pm at the high school gym. There will also be a parent/player meeting this Sunday at 6pm in the High School/Middle School lunch room. Practices are scheduled for 7-9pm every Sunday through the month of February (7 practices).

As in years past, there is a $100 player fee that covers team insurance, state registration fees, umpire costs, and equipment costs. The player fee must be paid before the February 3rd practice starts. You can certainly pay before that time, but if a player is up in the air, this will give them three practices to try it out without having to pay.

Players are required to wear indoor shoes for practice to protect the gym floor.

Any questions, please contact myself:

Eric Hortness

chiphort1976@gmail.com

605-760-0621
